8 An Act relating to education; creating the Federal
Education Guidance Disclosure Act; requiring the
9 State Department of Education to publish certain
documents on a website; prescribing publication
10 timeframe; construing website creation timeline;
mandating use of hyperlinks; directing retention of
11 certain rescinded documents; stating retention
requirements; defining term; providing for
12 codification; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Federal
20 Education Guidance Disclosure Act".
21 B. Within five (5) days of receiving a guidance document from
22 the United States Department of Education, the State Department of
23 Education shall publish the guidance document on an Internet website
24 designated by the State Superintendent of Public Instruction unless
Req. No. 12986 Page 1

1 the guidance document contains sensitive or confidential information
2 not legal to disclose due to privacy laws.
3 C. 1. The State Department of Education shall create the
4 designated Internet website for publication described in subsection
5 B of this section no later than ninety (90) days after the effective
6 date of this act.
7 2. The State Department of Education shall include hyperlinks
8 on the Internet website, in a conspicuous manner, that provide
9 access to the guidance documents received pursuant to subsection B
10 of this section.
11 D. If a guidance document is rescinded by the United States
12 Department of Education, the State Department of Education shall
13 maintain the rescinded guidance document at the location described
14 in subsection C of this section and indicate within fifteen (15)
15 days of such rescission:
16 1. That the document has been rescinded; and
17 2. The date the document was rescinded.
18 E. For purposes of this section, "guidance document" means a
19 federal agency statement of general applicability, other than a rule
20 that has the force and effect of law promulgated in accordance with
21 the notice and comment procedures under 5 U.S.C., Section 553, that
22 is designated by an agency official as setting forth a policy or
23 interpretation on a statutory, regulatory, or technical issue. A
24 guidance document may include, but is not limited to, a memorandum,
Req. No. 12986 Page 2

1 noti ce, bulletin, directive, letter, or no-action letter. The term
2 guidance document shall be construed broadly to effectuate the
3 purpose and intent of this act.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
